parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission control module can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates to shift gears
the vehicle stalls
the "Electronic Throttle Control System Should Be Serviced" warning indicator illuminates
the vehicle loses power
the transmission shifts abruptly
the vehicle slows down or accelerates unexpectedly.

the vehicle does not engage into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive shaft can cause the vehicle to vibrate or lose power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall notice may indicate a potential issue with the airbag system, which can lead to accidents or injuries if not addressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag deployment failures can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
